  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The first dimension is independent versus collaborative, where independent innovation emerges from individual effort, while collaborative innovation requires coordination among multiple contributors (Singh and Fleming 2010).",
    "The other dimension is voluntary versus guided, where the former stems from self-selected participation, and the latter occurs with explicit direction within organizational structures (Felin and Zenger 2014).",
    "Voluntary collaborative settings have the greatest potential for technological augmentation as contributors can rapidly adapt their innovation strategies without organizational constraints (Hippel and Krogh 2003; Shah 2006).",
    "The voluntary collaborative context creates unique dynamics for capability and iterative innovation types.",
    "Without formal direction, contributors must independently identify valuable opportunities and navigate complex social structures to integrate their work."
  ],
